+++++++++++++++++++++IMPORTANT+++++++++++++++++++++

When you query the vulnerability_instances collection, you can filter by metadata fields. For example, if you want to find all instances of "database injection" with severity "HIGH", you can do:
collection.query(
    query_texts=["database injection"],
    where={"severity": "HIGH"},
    n_results=5
)

Chroma does:

Embed "database injection"

Find nearest embeddings (vector similarity)

Filter those by severity == HIGH

Return matching documents + metadata